# Agent Autonomy

This repo is operated entirely by the agent. The user sets vision; the agent executes.

## Rules

1. Run `yarn verify` (or `scripts/verify.sh`) before declaring done
2. Use CLIs (`supabase`, `vercel`, `gh`, `yarn`) — not service dashboards
3. Pause only at documented user gates in `docs/prerequisites.md` (account creation, `.env.local` secrets)
4. Self-fix CI failures; never ask the user to triage logs
5. Propagate secrets from `.env.local` via CLI — user does not configure GitHub/Vercel manually

## User gates (only these)

- GitHub repo ownership
- Supabase project creation
- Vercel account / project link
- Filling `.env.local` with API keys
